of the affect and ethics of ritual animal sacrifice, analysis of the right-wing political project of cow-protection, or examination of villagers’ talk about bears who abduct women and have sex with them, Govindrajan illustrates that multispecies relatedness relies on both difference and ineffable affinity between animals. Animal Intimacies breaks substantial new ground in animal studies, and Govindrajan’s detailed portrait of the social, political and religious life of the region will be of interest to cultural anthropologists and scholars of South Asia as well.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAnimalszIndiazUttarakhandxReligious aspects. 0aAnimals-India-Uttarakhand-Religious aspects. 0aHuman-animal relationshipszIndiazUttarakhand. 0aHuman-animal relationships-India-Uttarakhand. 0aWildlife conservationzIndiazUttarakhand. 0aWildlife conservation-India-Uttarakhand. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aHimalayas.  aHinduism.  aSouth Asia.  aagrarian studies.  aconservation.  aenvironmental anthropology.  agender and sexuality.  ahuman-animal relations.  akinship.  amultispecies ethnography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106885800 cprintz978022655984140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226560045423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226560045/original  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles